The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Reliance Comm merger

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, June 5: Reliance Communication Ventures (RCoVL) has secured shareholders nod for the merger of nine companies under the Anil Dhirubhai Ambani group with itself. Shareholders of RCoVL have also cleared plans to sponsor an American Depository Receipts/Global Depository Receipts offering of up to $1 billion and a change in its name to Reliance Communications.

 In a letter to the bourses today, the company said shareholders have approved with requisite majority, both in value and number, the scheme of amalgamation. 




